---
// Home panel — landing hero and overview columns
---

<section id="panel-home" class="panel">
    <div class="landing-hero">
        <h1>
            <span style="color: var(--fg-main); text-shadow: 0 0 25px rgba(232, 224, 208, 0.4);">Tyler Myles</span>
            <span class="hero-subtitle">Unreal Engine Game Developer & Audio Engineer</span>
        </h1>
    </div>

    <div class="home-columns">
        <div class="data-block">
            <h3>Game Development</h3>
            <p>
                I specialize in Unreal Engine as a gameplay and systems programmer. While my primary
                expertise lies in C++, my background as a solo developer and freelance contractor ensures
                proficiency across the entire Unreal Engine ecosystem — from Blueprints, custom material
                nodes, and Slate UI to technical art tools, netcode, and prediction rollback systems.
            </p>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 15px; align-items: center; margin-top: auto;">
                <a href="#panel-dev" class="btn-action" title="View game development portfolio and shipped projects">Explore Development</a>
                <a class="btn-action" href="/Tyler_Myles_Resume.pdf" download="Tyler_Myles_Resume.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" title="Download Tyler Myles Game Developer Resume (PDF)">Download CV</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="data-block">
            <h3>Audio Production</h3>
            <p>
                I provide modern metal mixing, mastering, composition, and songwriting. Every track is
                designed for impact, quality, and industry streaming standards. Whether it's streaming on
                Spotify,
                Apple Music, or YouTube, your music will sound loud and professional.
            </p>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 15px; align-items: center; margin-top: auto;">
                <a href="#panel-prod" class="btn-action">Explore Audio</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
